he same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":27,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Peter Maulever was born about 1355, in Beamsley, Yorkshire, England, his father, William Mauleverer, was 26 and his mother, Catharine Boswell, was 26. He had at least 2 sons and 4 daughters with Lady Katherine Maulever. He died about 22 May 1398, at the age of 44."},"et":{"about 1355–about 22 May 1398":"umbes 1355–umbes 22. mai 1398","1355–1398":"1355–1398","1360–1443":"1360–1443","1360–Female":"1360–Surnud","1378–Female":"1378–Surnud","1382–1430":"1382–1430","–1395":"–1395","–1399":"–1399","–1400":"–1400","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1330–Female":"1330–Surnud","1330":"1330","1395":"1395","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","about 22 May 1398":"umbes 22. mai 1398","1378":"1378","1400":"1400","1399":"1399","1443":"1443","1355":"1355","1398":"1398","1430":"1430","after 10 March 1395":"pärast 10. märtsi 1395","about 1355":"umbes 1355","Arncliffe, Yorkshire, England":"Arncliffe, Yorkshire, England","Beamsley, Yorkshire, England":"Beamsley, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1355–about 22 May 1398":"noin 1355–noin 22. toukokuuta 1398","1355–1398":"1355–1398","1360–1443":"1360–1443","1360–F